{"questionId":"21324","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The Voronoi diagram below shows three identical cellular phone towers, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>T</mtext><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>T</mtext><mn>2</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>T</mtext><mn>3</mn></math>.&nbsp;A fourth identical cellular phone tower, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>T</mtext><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp;is located in the shaded region. The dashed lines in the&nbsp;diagram below represent the edges in the Voronoi diagram.</p>\n<p>Horizontal scale: <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> unit represents <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>km</mtext></math>.<br>Vertical scale: <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;unit represents&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>km</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/7ac9c27733d36485d3c05f79490cb0365a5b8612.png\"></p>\n<p>Tim stands inside the shaded region.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Explain why Tim will receive the strongest signal from tower <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>T4</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>every point in the shaded region is closer to tower&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>T4</mtext></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Specific reference must be made to the closeness of tower <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>T4</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;<em><strong><br>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21324","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ1.5a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Explain why Tim will receive the strongest signal from tower T4.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Voronoi diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}